This paper deals with the problem of eliciting and aggregating probabilistic information from multiple agents, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also leverages techniques from Bayesian statistics, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with proper scoring rules, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT).
